<Base title="VoiceLog — Privacy Policy">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>VoiceLog — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: 2026-05-05</p>

    <p>VoiceLog is built by BroooApps. Privacy is the product — here's how it works.</p>

    <h2>Data we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Voice recordings and transcripts</strong> — stored locally on your device. Never uploaded.</li>
      <li><strong>Anonymous usage analytics</strong> — crash reports and broad usage patterns. No personal identifiers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>On-device processing</h2>
    <p>Speech-to-text and AI summarisation run on your device using on-device models (Whisper / Gemini Nano). Your voice and transcripts do not leave your phone.</p>

    <h2>What we never do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Upload your recordings to a server.</li>
      <li>Sell or share your data.</li>
      <li>Collect your name, email, contacts, or location.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>Delete recordings individually in the app, or wipe everything by uninstalling.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:swapniltiwari775@gmail.com">swapniltiwari775@gmail.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
